  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age at least 21 years and no more than 80 years

          -  Resistant hypertension despite optimal, stable antihypertensive medications for at
             least 4 weeks

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Significant carotid plaque or stenosis

          -  Known or suspected baroreflex failure or autonomic neuropathy

          -  Significant renal disease requiring dialysis

          -  Myocardial infarction, unstable angina, syncope, or cerebral vascular accident within
             the past 3 months

          -  Secondary hypertension
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
